    {
        "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442444",
        "quote": "When I was a child, we always had wine on the table, no matter how simple the meal. The wine had no special identity; it was just 'the wine,' from the cellar cask. The rules were general: white with the first course, red with the main course.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Jacques Pepin",
            "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442444"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Simple",
