                "name": "Bottle",
                "url": "/topics/bottle"
            },
            {
                "name": "By The Time",
                "url": "/topics/by_the_time"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442426",
        "quote": "My mother likes what I cook, but doesn't think it's French. My wife is Puerto Rican and Cuban, so I eat rice and beans. We have a place in Mexico, but people think I'm the quintessential French chef.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Jacques Pepin",
            "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442426"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Think",
                "url": "/topics/think"
            },
            {
                "name": "Cook",
                "url": "/topics/cook"
            },
            {
                "name": "Quintessential",
                "url": "/topics/quintessential"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442427",
        "quote": "I was chef to the French Presidents between '56 and '59, finished with de Gaulle, and during de Gaulle I remember serving Eisenhower, Nehru, Tito, Macmillan; those were the heads of state at the time. I never saw anyone. No one would ever, ever, ever come to the kitchen. You couldn't even see them.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Jacques Pepin",
            "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442427"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "I Remember",
                "url": "/topics/i_remember"
            },
            {
                "name": "Presidents",
                "url": "/topics/presidents"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442428",
        "quote": "I cooked at the White House for Easter, last year, with Michelle Obama. But it more had to do with cooking from the organic garden, and her message. I took my daughter and granddaughter there, and they were really charming, it was great.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Jacques Pepin",
            "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442428"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Year",
                "url": "/topics/year"
            },
            {
                "name": "Last Year",
                "url": "/topics/last_year"
            },
            {
                "name": "Michelle",
                "url": "/topics/michelle"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442430",
        "quote": "You know, my parents had a restaurant. And I left home, actually, in 1949, when I was 13 years old, to go into apprenticeship. And actually when I left home, home was a restaurant - like I said, my mother was a chef. So I can't remember any time in my life, from age 5, 6, that I wasn't in a kitchen.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Jacques Pepin",
            "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442430"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "My Life",
                "url": "/topics/my_life"
            },
            {
                "name": "Years",
                "url": "/topics/years"
            },
            {
                "name": "Had",
                "url": "/topics/had"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442431",
        "quote": "Probably a mistake, you know, that people make in America, to think that all great chefs are a male... I'm still the only male in the family who went into that business.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Jacques Pepin",
            "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442431"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Mistake",
                "url": "/topics/mistake"
            },
            {
                "name": "Think",
                "url": "/topics/think"
            },
            {
                "name": "Still",
                "url": "/topics/still"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442432",
        "quote": "When I left to go into apprenticeship in 1949, it was only four years after the war, and people don't realize, we still had tickets for butter, meat and so forth in France until 1947. It's not like the end of the war, everything was plentiful - it wasn't.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Jacques Pepin",
            "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442432"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Years",
                "url": "/topics/years"
            },
            {
                "name": "Had",
                "url": "/topics/had"
            },
            {
                "name": "Tickets",
                "url": "/topics/tickets"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442433",
        "quote": "Thirty, 40 years ago, more than that now, even, the cook was certainly at the bottom of the social scale. And any mother would've wanted their child to marry a doctor, a lawyer, an architect, not a cook. Now, we are genius, it's different.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Jacques Pepin",
            "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442433"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Scale",
                "url": "/topics/scale"
            },
            {
                "name": "Architect",
                "url": "/topics/architect"
            },
            {
                "name": "Marry",
                "url": "/topics/marry"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442435",
        "quote": "I have an immigrant story. Most people come here for economic reasons, or religious reasons, or racial reasons, or gender reasons, or one of those things. I had a good job in Paris, but America was, and still is, the golden fleece. And I've done very well!",
        "author": {
            "name": "Jacques Pepin",
            "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442435"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Religious",
                "url": "/topics/religious"
            },
            {
                "name": "Here",
                "url": "/topics/here"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442438",
        "quote": "Most people who came here came for economic reasons or sometimes for religious or political reasons. I didn't have any of this. I came here, I liked it, I stayed. So I'm a pure American - even more than people who are born here - because I did it by choice as an adult.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Jacques Pepin",
            "url": "/quotes/jacques_pepin_442438"
        },
